folder: Sullivan Street & Prince Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Sullivan Street (through the center), north from Prince Street (across the foreground), showing in View No. 1 the west side of the street and in No. 2 the east side. The two Prince Street structures shown at the left are No's 191 and 193, at and adjoining the N.W.
corner of Sullivan Street.
May 7, 1928.
P. L. Sperr .

folder: Prince Street & Sullivan Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Prince Street, east from Sullivan Street, showing demolition work in progress on three houses, Nos. 175 to 171, west of, adjoining and at the N.W. corner of Thompson Street. Also shown is a portion of the Sixth Ave. Elevated Line on West Broadway.
May 20, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
